 be clearly placed in the early Peripatetic setting, that the physiological section, which follows, has a background of school practice in dialectical argument, that the main authorities "ed in the text (Herophilus, Erasistratus and Asclepiades) have different roles (Herophilus’s is the most positive) but the authors always feels at liberty to confute their opinions and treats them as characters of the same scientific context.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Greek, Ancient (to 1453).0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aMedicinexPhilosophyvEarly works to 1800. 0aMedicine, Greek and RomanvEarly works to 1800. 0aMedicine, Greek and Roman. 4aAltertumswissenschaft. 4aGriechische Texte. 4aKlassische Philosophie. 4aPapyrologie. 7aMEDICAL / History.2bisacsh  aPapyrology, Ancient Science and Medicine, Ancient philosophy, Greek texts.1 aManetti, Daniela, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Medicine and Life Sciences 2000 - 2014z9783110637915oZDB-23-GML08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2010z9783110233575oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311021871840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311023903440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110239034423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110239034/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2010  aZDB-23-DGGb2010  aZDB-23-GMLc2000d2014